PGA Tour Stats Database

Using data from the PGA Tour website, I have created a database of the 2022/23 season player statistics (update as of June 21st).

Database connection

pga_stats <- DBI::dbConnect(
  drv = RSQLite::SQLite(),
  dbname = here::here("data", "pga_stats.db")
)

DBI::dbListTables(pga_stats)
## [1] "birdies_per_round" "driving_distance"  "gir_pct"          
## [4] "scoring_avg"       "scrambling_pct"

Formatting & cleaning tables

Here, we create dataframes from the database connection, and use janitor::clean_names() to tidy the column names

birdies <- data.frame(
  dplyr::tbl(pga_stats, "birdies_per_round")
  ) %>% 
  janitor::clean_names()

driving <- data.frame(
  dplyr::tbl(pga_stats, "driving_distance")
  ) %>% 
  janitor::clean_names()

gir <- data.frame(
  dplyr::tbl(pga_stats, "gir_pct")
  ) %>% 
  janitor::clean_names()

scoring <- data.frame(
  dplyr::tbl(pga_stats, "scoring_avg")
  ) %>% 
  janitor::clean_names()

scrambling <- data.frame(
  dplyr::tbl(pga_stats, "scrambling_pct")
  ) %>% 
  janitor::clean_names()
birdies <- birdies %>% 
  select(-movement) %>% 
  rename(birdies_per_round = avg)

driving <- driving %>% 
  select(-movement) %>% 
  rename(driving_avg = avg)

gir <- gir %>% 
  select(-movement) %>% 
  rename(gir_pct = x)

scoring <- scoring %>% 
  select(-movement) %>% 
  rename(scoring_avg = avg)

scrambling <- scrambling %>% 
  select(-movement) %>% 
  rename(scrambling_pct = x)
